article.description: Ruben Patterson scored 10 of his 15 points in the fourth quarter and Daniels also scored 15 off the bench as the Trail Blazers ended a six-game losing streak in Denver with a 94-84 victory over the Nuggets on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Blazers' starters get lift from energetic bench
article.linkText: Blazers find bench relief in toppling Nuggets
article.story:
DENVER (AP) -- With Scottie Pippen sitting out and Portland's other starters struggling, the Trail Blazers needed some relief from the bench. Ruben Patterson and Antonio Daniels provided it. Patterson scored 10 of his 15 points in the fourth quarter and Daniels also scored 15 off the bench as the Trail Blazers ended a six-game losing streak in Denver with a 94-84 victory over the Nuggets on Wednesday night. "Our starters just didn't have any energy,'' Portland coach Maurice Cheeks said. "They were flat from playing last night, and the guys on the bench were ready to play, and eager to play, hadn't played a whole lot of minutes, and when you are thrust in that type of position the guys are just ready.'' Portland's bench outscored its counterparts 53-27. They needed to with Pippen (sore knee) sidelined and Rasheed Wallace having played 45 minutes the night before. "There was no secret to the lineup I put out on the floor,'' Cheeks said. "It was just guys that hadn't played a whole lot, and just had a lot of energy.'' Patterson shot 5-for-6 in the final quarter, and Daniels hit a 3-pointer to start a game-deciding 9-0 run as the Trail Blazers won in Denver for the first time since Nov. 12, 1999. "I was in a little bit of a groove,'' Patterson said. "I tried to change things around for us, being aggressive, getting to the basket and scoring, stealing the ball, and when everybody saw me working hard, they started working hard.'' Juwan Howard had 26 points and Donnell Harvey added 22 for the Nuggets, who matched a season high with their 10th straight loss. Junior Harrington had a double-double with 12 points and 13 rebounds. "We made some key mistakes at the end, and it was as if we deferred and looked for others to make the play,'' Denver coach Jeff Bzdelik said. "We run the marathon, are in the lead and then in the final two miles we defer and stop.'' Howard gave Denver its last lead, 82-80 before the Trail Blazers regained it on Daniels 3-pointer. Damon Stoudamire and Ruben Patterson followed with baskets off turnovers and Patterson added a breakaway dunk when Howard lost the ball to put Portland ahead 91-82. The Nuggets managed only Howard's jumper in the last 3:58 after taking a 71-63 lead into the final quarter. Portland caught the Nuggets at 78-78 on Patterson's two free throws with 6:18 left. The Nuggets made a move in the third quarter, outscoring the Trail Blazers 27-19 in the period. After falling behind 49-48 on the second of two jump shots by Bonzi Wells, Harrington hit four straight free throws and contributed a steal and six points in an 11-2 run to build a 59-51 lead with 6:47 left. Harvey connected on two jump shots to make it 67-54 with 4:02 remaining. Daniels 3-pointer narrowed the lead to 71-63 after three quarters. The game was tied five times in the second quarter and 44-44 at the break on a jumper by Wells. Harvey's dunk gave Denver its biggest lead of the period, 30-27. "I had some pretty good looks,'' said Harvey, who came within a point of his career high of 23. "I took advantage of my opportunities and my shots were falling.''

Game notes
Portland C Dale Davis played after missing Tuesday's game because of an upper respiratory infection. ... Wallace had a 2-for-7 start with two airballs on 3-pointers. ... Portland turned 22 Denver turnovers into 35 points. ... The Nuggets waived guard Chris Whitney and activated Predrag Savovic from the injured list. Denver forward Ryan Bowen took a knee to the stomach and was taken to a hospital for precautionary X-rays that showed no serious injury.
